	</div><div class="blogs_entrybody" style="clear:both">
		I could hear his footsteps coming down the hall; rhythmic, squeaky, and filled with anticipation.  Jonathan Allison rounded the corner and practically leapt into the storage room that we called headquarters.<br/>"Chief, Scrap ... I don't believe that I know this other person." Jonathan said as he extended his hand to Jon.<br/><br/>"Jon is a surveillance expert.  The best I've ever worked with." I said as I inflated Jon's already enormous ego another ten p.s.i.  "Jonathan, Scrap &amp; Jon have some tasks to do.  Can we talk in your office?" <br/><br/>"Certainly." Jonathan replied as he lead the way to his office.<br/><br/>I closed the door to Jonathan's office behind me and created a butt impression on a nearby leather chair.<br/><br/>"You said this was urgent?" Jonathan asked as he folded his arms neatly on his desk.  <br/><br/>"Is anything wrong?"<br/><br/>I shot Jonathan my best poker face, my eyes revealing nothing. <br/><br/>"There's very clearly something going on here at Allison Technologies.  There is an organized effort to steal magnetic backup tapes placed in your care and resell them on the second-hand market." I began.  "And somehow, Jonathan, I think you already knew that." <br/><br/>Jonathan stared at his desk.<br/><br/>"Perhaps." <br/><br/>I raised my voice slightly.  "And 'perhaps' you left out several critical facts from this case, like your brother being an employee?"<br/><br/>Jonathan continued to stare a hole through the desk with his incredible powers of concentration.<br/><br/>"You hired me to investigate the disappearance of company assets.  I know who's involved, I know what assets are being removed from the premises, I think I even understand their business plan.  But what I don't understand is why am I here in the first place?" I asked.<br/><br/>Jonathan peered up at me, obviously aware of his need to 'come clean'. <br/><br/>"Chief, first off, let me say that I now know why you come so highly recommended.  In a matter of a week you figured out a situation that took me months to uncover.  However, things are much more complex than you may think." Jonathan said quietly as he stood up and walked towards the window in his office.<br/><br/>"Jeffry?" I queried.<br/><br/>"Jeffry.  Jeffry is my brother.  I love my brother, but he's completely worthless.  If it wasn't for me giving Jeffry jobs and bailing him out of jail in his younger years he'd probably be sharing a cell with a car thief right about now.  Jeffry is the youngest sibling I have, Chief.  Everyone in my family feels sorry for Jeffry, and respects me for giving him a job.  However, when I mentioned to my parents that Jeffry was screwing up again and stealing from me, they became upset and told me to overlook his faults.  They told me to transfer him to another job and give him another chance." Jonathan lamented, his voice full of disgust.<br/><br/>"You didn't want to be the bad guy in a bad situation.  You bring me in as a consultant, and I uncover the great scheme to make money on the side at work." I said.<br/><br/>"Correct.  I could terminate Jeffry and his coworkers and not be the bad guy.  Most of Jeffry's coworkers are friends of his that I hired as a favor to Jeffry." Jonathan replied.<br/><br/>"What about Jose?  Jose was most helpful, and appears to be cooperating with the others out of fear?" I asked Jonathan.<br/><br/>"Jose has worked here a long time, and I know that Jeffry bullies him.  Jose has a huge family to support, and Jeffry know that; and he exploits that.  He's a good guy, and I plan on taking care of him." Jonathan said as he peered out of the window.<br/><br/>I breathed a sigh of relief.  Jose had been cooperating with me under the assumption that Jonathan would seek no retribution against him.  This was good news.<br/><br/>I suddenly remembered that I should be reviewing my notes on my notepad and actively engaging Jonathan in conversation, rather than daydreaming.<br/><br/>"My team and I have performed a lot of research and field work in the past week.  We know that customer tapes are being removed from your trucks and placed in a garage that belongs to Tomas' brother Jerry.  Jerry owns a computer recycling business.  My associate, Scrap, visited Jerry's recycle center yesterday and located one of ten tapes that we had tagged with a dye marker.  The tape was one of many that we found in the boxes that we opened in the truck earlier in the week.  Careful examination of the tape showed that data from one of your customers was present.  We're talking one serious exposure of customer data." I said as I flipped through several more pages of notes.<br/><br/>"Yes, you are correct.  The guys ... they all knew the procedures  here well enough that they knew how to safely get around them.  They were targeting companies that shipped us almost brand-new high-capacity tapes for destruction.  The tapes were typically in a storage rotation of a year's cycle, from what I could tell.   The tapes that they wanted to steal were scanned into the system as received using the driver's gun, and then Jose would mark them as 'en route' in the system so they wouldn't come up missing.  The tapes were driven to Jerry's house, and then the boxes were returned with a few tapes clanging around in the bottom.  When the tape boxes came back and were checked back in, the destroyers simply opened the boxes, scanned the remaining tapes in the box, and ran them through the destruction machines.  Our system always showed the tapes as destroyed.  That's what made it so hard for me to track down initially." Jonathan said as he sat back down.  <br/><br/>"Well, I can't say this has been the most entertaining goose chase I've ever been on.  You have quite the barrel of monkeys here, Jonathan.  I hope you have a good attorney on retainer and a strong management team behind you.  You have a few customers that aren't going to be happy when they find out that their backup tapes were being sold as second-hand flea market specials." I said.<br/><br/>Jonathan was looking more stressed as I spoke.<br/><br/>"However, my team will have a report complete with electronic media delivered to you on Monday afternoon.  I'll send you a bill for the remainder of my fee and expenses." I said as I got up from my chair and wandered towards the door.<br/><br/>"Thanks for all your hard work." Jonathan said as sprang from his chair and shook my hand.  "I'm sorry I didn't tell you everything at the beginning of this, but I didn't know if you'd stick around after you heard the whole story." <br/><br/>"No worries Jonathan.  You and the rest of your management team will have all the ammunition you need in the reports and video files on Monday.  Oh, and Jonathan ..." I said as I opened the door.<br/><br/>"Yes?" Jonathan asked curiously.<br/><br/>I reached into my pocket and tossed Jonathan the Allison Technologies badge and lanyard that Scrap and I had lifted earlier in the week.<br/><br/>"You might want to give this employee back her badge." <br/><br/>***<br/><br/>Scrap and I practically did cartwheels after we left AT for the last time.  We were very eager to completely wash our hands of this case.  As a very clever reader noted in a comment on our last case file posting, this was a case of family politics.  Jeffry was the bad seed, Jonathan wanted to fire him but didn't want the pressure of being the bad guy.<br/><br/>Jonathan, along with his two attorneys, started a marathon of contacting law enforcement, having Jeffry, Tomas, Pah &amp; Jerry arrested for theft and sale of stolen goods, Jeffry, Tomas &amp; Pah were obviously terminated immediately (Jonathan was careful to delete their badge access), and several law suits were filed against AT by customers over the theft of their tapes and potential information disclosure.  <br/><br/>New case file next week!<br/><br/>~ Chief<p><hr><table width="100%" bgcolor="#FFFFCC" cellpadding="9px">
