				The moral of the story is to not put people who aren't reliable=
 and with a criminal history in positions of trust - regardless=
 of whether they're relatives or not=2E 

I know of another instance where a company hired a "past" fraud=
 artist - as their book-keeper! "She's reformed" was one reason=
 given for hiring her=2E Turns out she figured out how to forge=
 signatures within a week of being hired=2E There wasn't sufficient=
 controls in place to catch such conduct, and she wasn't found=
 out until one of the partners opened an AMex bill - for $45K=2E

When all was said and done, it turns out she'd embezzeled such a=
 large amount of money from the company that after it was sold,=
 all the partners came out wth a net of - nothing=2E

Hopefully AT survives all the lawsuits and the owner learns a=
 very expensive lesson=2E

Tim Kuehn


